body: I chose to get radish seeds. I put them into 9 cups, 3 seeds in each to ensure at least one will survive and grow. The cups that I chose to put in the high light area are on my kitchen window sill, they are in blue cups. The medium light ones are on my kitchen table. The low light cups are in my bathroom, on my sink counter, which only has a small window that is blocked by the shower, so the main source of light for these seeds will be artificial. Having three cups per location will help to keep the experiment's results accurate. I plan to measure the results first by sight and then to measure the growth of the plants. I believe that the radish's that are in my kitchen window will grow the fastest and the best since they have access to the best and largest amount of light through the day.

• What type of seeds did you plant?

Bush Beans

  • Explain the importance of including three cups containing three seeds each in each treatment location.

This helps to control variables in the experiment.

  • Describe the three experimental locations that you have selected.

I placed "high" in my greenhouse (18hr direct sunlight)

I placed "mid" on my window (9hr direct sunlight)

I placed "low" on my basement window (0hr direct sunlight

  • Explain how you plan to monitor and measure the effect of light intensity on plant growth. 

By measuring the plants every 2 days minimum after germination. 

  • What is your hypothesis?

The rate of growth will be in line with the rate of sunlight the plant gets.
